The paper deals with the capacity limit and noise in fibre optical communication systems, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a noise model and characterizes correlations among channels, which are topics related to optics (cs.OH) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the transmission throughput, which is a topic related to physical-layer communication (cs.PH).
